      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Finding peace doesn't have to be a temporary distraction. It's about accepting the reality of your situation and finding a way to live with it. Stopping isn't always the answer, and sometimes, it's about finding a way to cope with the pain and suffering. The universe may seem empty, but that doesn't mean you're alone in your struggles. There are people who care about you and want to help, even if it doesn't always feel that way. And sometimes, it's okay to just be, to let go of the fight, and to find your own way to peace, even if it's not what you expected.",
